        <h1>Privacy Policy for QuitX: Quit Smoking</h1>
        <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> September 10, 2025</p>

        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>Welcome to QuitX: Quit Smoking ("we," "our," or "us"). We are deeply committed to supporting you on your journey to a smoke-free life and protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application ("App"). By using our App, you agree to the practices described herein.</p>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>To provide and enhance our services, we may collect the following types of information:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> Information you provide, such as your name or email address if you choose to create an account.</li>
            <li><strong>Quit Progress Data:</strong> Information related to your quitting journey, such as your quit date, number of cigarettes avoided, money saved, and cravings tracked. This data is essential for the App's functionality.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Details about your interactions with the App, including features accessed and time spent, to help us improve the user experience.</li>
            <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Data about the device used to access the App, such as device model and operating system, to ensure compatibility and for troubleshooting.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Permissions Requested</h2>
        <p>To deliver its full range of features, our App requests the following permissions:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>INTERNET</code>: Enables the App to access the internet for features like data backup (if applicable), community support, and retrieving motivational content.</li>
            <li><code>VIBRATE</code>: Allows the App to use haptic feedback for notifications, alerts, and celebrating your milestones.</li>
            <li><code>POST_NOTIFICATIONS</code>: Permits the App to send you motivational messages, progress reminders, and achievement alerts to keep you on track.</li>
            <li><code>CAMERA</code>: Allows you to optionally use your camera to personalize your profile with a photo or to document your journey with progress pictures. Usage of the camera is initiated by you.</li>
            <li><code>RECORD_AUDIO</code>: Enables you to optionally record voice notes or motivational messages for yourself. Usage of the microphone is initiated by you.</li>
            <li><code>READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE</code> & <code>WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE</code>: Allows the App to save and access data you create, such as exported progress reports, photos, or audio notes, on your device's storage.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We utilize the collected information to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Provide and Maintain Services:</strong> Track your progress, calculate your health benefits, and ensure the App functions correctly.</li>
            <li><strong>Improve User Experience:</strong> Analyze usage patterns to enhance App features, performance, and motivational content.</li>
            <li><strong>Communicate with You:</strong> Send notifications, updates, and support messages related to your quitting journey.</li>
            <li><strong>Personalize Your Experience:</strong> Allow you to customize your profile and journey with your own photos and audio recordings.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Sharing Your Information</h2>
        <p>We value your trust and do not sell your personal data. We do not share your personal information with third parties, except in the following situations:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>With Your Consent:</strong> We may share information when you provide explicit consent.</li>
            <li><strong>For Legal Obligations:</strong> We may disclose information to comply with legal requirements or protect our rights.</li>
            <li><strong>With Service Providers:</strong> We may engage trusted third-party vendors for services like data analysis or customer support. These providers are contractually obligated to protect your information and use it solely for the services they offer on our behalf.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement robust security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or destruction. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.</p>

        <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have rights concerning your personal data, including the right to access, correct, or delete your information within the App. For any requests or questions about your data, please contact us.</p>

        <h2>8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy within the App or on our website and updating the "Effective Date." We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy regularly.</p>

        <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p>
        <p>
            <strong>[Your Company Name]</strong><br>
            <a href="mailto:[basithedev@gmail.com]">[basithedev@gmail.com]</a>
        </p>
